# Food pics!

The bread recipe we used was a bit small for the cast iron pot I used, so it came out a bit flat.

![Photo of a short loaf of bread we made](&Szk9+0Kf/1+UvbbN3VTnnv6viXBkzWRiOjVDrAbw+r0=.sha256)

Still tasted great thought! I added lots of sesame seeds and it had a really nice flavor.

![Cross-section photo of short loaf of bread](&iX/iEXxlvZgcAo3lJ93S1SDY3y4IU7WFClJvBm9C9dc=.sha256)

Kathleen's also been making a bunch of lasagnas lately and I'm loving it. Here's one with a tofu ricotta she made with the food processor! 

![Photo of another lasagna that Kathleen made, red sauce with white-ish yellow tofu dollops](&z5f/LZwUOyEofdggMdDfGoS9yQvXUPusoo1EGjYNFjQ=.sha256)

## Bonus round

Does cider count as "food"? I think yes.

![Photo of Kathleen enjoying a cider](&qQk4fRKqvyHVyRAw3As8dM24bc3VDrrmaaXSm4myBqQ=.sha256)
